import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='u', y='v', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='u', data=data)
    mean_u = data['u'].mean()
    plt.axvline(mean_u, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {mean_u:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the mean of u?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='v')
    std_v = data['v'].std()
    plt.axhline(y=std_v, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Standard Deviation: {std_v:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the standard deviation of v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
